<section class="W-SD">
  <h2 class="Project-Nature">Photography / Production / Portrait</h2>
  <h3>Portraits of Felix Wong</h3>
  <p>
    This photography project was marketing orientated and commercial.
    Even though it was huge and important, the process of photo shooting was joyful, interactive and memorable.
  </p>


  <h3>Interaction with Felix 黃日華</h3>
  <p class="em1-25 gtbm" style="color: black;">
    『一開始唔使笑住，留返等陣慢慢。』
    <br>
    "Don't have to smile now. Save it for later."
  </p>
  <p>
    Felix is a very experienced actor. His reflex actions took him to those epic postures spontaneously,
    like James-Bond-style facial expressions, classic smile, gentleman moves, etc.
    However, I needed many different styles from those ordery presentations for future marketing materials.
    He was professional and responded to my preference accurately. I directed this shooting smoothly.
    I’d like to acknowledge the effort of every production party:
    Joseph Lai (Advertising Agency),
    Lawrence Mak (Photographer) & his crews,
    Jeff Tong & William Fung (Videographers),
    and, of course, my very best designers - Mavis Cheung (in early stage), Jojo Chung & Suki Sze-To.
  </p>
</section>

